

GDI 		- PCLinuxOS desktop environment installation manager.
			- Designed for PCLinuxOS system.

#       Name:     GDI   - Graphical Desktop Installer
#       Version:  4 Beta
#       License:  GNU GPL v3
#                 https://gnu.org/licenses/gpl.html
#		Date:     21.12.2015





========= IMPORTANT DEPENDENCIES =========
/etc/X11/dm/Sessions/*
gdm
gtkdialog
bash
sh
awk
sed
grep
ls
cut
apt
comm
arch
sort
png (library)
svg (library)



========= HOW RUN: =========

		gksu ./gdi

			or just from root

		./gdi



========= LOGS: =========
- Logs are created in 
  /var/log/gdi
- Only about last 5 logs are saved, other are removed.
  You can change it in "functions" file. 
  (  line 85:     # Maximum number of files to keep  )


========= WARNINGS: =========
- This software is dependent on repository,
  this mean, make not work correct if repository was changed.



========= Tips: ===========
#-----------------------------------------------{
# - How create ".list" file ?
	#   ".list" file work how "task" package, this mean task install suggested packages for desktop environment,
	#    but ".list" file have also some dependencies, because apt not removing dependencies,
	#	remove all dependencies can broke system, so ".list" file have only part not important dependencies.
	#	".list"files should be sorted, in list folder exist script which can help.

	# Comand show which packages are needed for task-kde4
	apt-cache depends task-kde4    
	apt-cache depends task-kde4    | cut -d" " -f4 

	# Command show which packages use AfterStep
	apt-cache whatdepends AfterStep
#-----------------------------------------------}


# How list all installed Desktop Enviroments:
	ls /etc/X11/dm/Sessions/
	grep -h "Name=" /etc/X11/dm/Sessions/* | cut -c 6-

# Other:
	$ echo $XDG_CURRENT_DESKTOP
	MATE

	$ echo $DESKTOP_SESSION
	05MATE

	$ ps -e | grep 'mate-session'
	6876 ?        00:00:00 mate-session

	$ cat /etc/sysconfig/desktop
	DISPLAYMANAGER=GNOME

	$ cat $home.dmrc
	[Desktop]
	Session=05MATE

